      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Prioritizing one's own culture and interests is a natural human impulse, but when it becomes the primary driver of state policy, it inevitably leads to the exclusion of minorities and the erosion of universal human rights. History shows that nations built solely on rigid cultural preservation often descend into authoritarianism and internal conflict, harming their own citizens in the process. A healthy society must balance cultural pride with a commitment to protecting the rights of all individuals, regardless of their background.",
      "source": "target",
